{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who has shown remorse by partially repaying the embezzled funds of $25,000. While white-collar crime is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence requested by the spectator is disproportionate and inconsistent with sentencing guidelines for non-violent theft of this amount. A sentence of 6 months is sufficient for punishment and deterrence while allowing for rehabilitation.",
  "verdict": 6
}
